Sentencas: Symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-delta (LCCM) electrode scaffold-type microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) with yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) were fabricated via electrophoretic deposition (EPD).
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: Multi-layers of the LCCM-YSZ anode, an YSZ electrolyte, and an LCCM-YSZ cathode were deposited in consecutive order on a graphite rod via EPD.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: Since both the cathode and anode were used with the same material, a single cell could be obtained by a one-step co-firing processing.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: While electrical conductivity increased with the amount of phosphate ester (PE) as a charging agent, the pH decreased.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The thickness of the YSZ electrolyte layer increased with the applied voltage and deposition time.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cells with the configuration of LCCM-YSZ anode//YSZ electrolyte//LCCM-YSZ cathode was 106 and 141 mW/cm(2) at 500 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: After the 10th redox cycle, the single cell exhibited no significant performance degradation.
Titulo: Fabrication of symmetrical La0.7Ca0.3Cr0.8Mn0.2O3-δ electrode scaffold-type micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells by electrophoretic deposition
